@node Intro "Introduction.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}What is DRemind?@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

  DRemind is a reminder program.

  It is designed to be used for remembering long-term and reoccuring
  events such as birth days, anniversaries, daily/weekly TV-shows,
  dental appointment, when to pay the bills, etc.

  It is also very easy to add short-term reminds for things to do
  in only a few minutes or hours, such as remembering to take the
  steak out of the oven, remember to take the batteries of charging
  and things like that.

  When an event occurs it is possible to have a window open on the
  screen telling you about the event. You can also specify a CLI or
  ARexx command to be executed. This makes it possible to use
  DRemind for scheduling backups or any other task in the background.

    You name it, DRemind remembers it!

  DRemindPrefs is used to create reminds and DRemind will
  check when to remind you in the background.

  DRemind is not a calendar or filofax type of program where you
  can see the reminds in a calendar or something like that.


@endnode

@node Reqs "Requirements.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}What you need:@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

  This program requires OSVersion 37+.

  @{i}MUI - Magical User Interface @{ui}

  Also @{i}diskfont.library    v37+,
       commodities.library v37+,
       workbench.library   v37+,  @{ui}to use WB's Tools-menu
       @{i}datatypes.library   v39+,  @{ui}if you want to use the DRemind.image
  and  @{i}locale.libaray      v37+   @{ui}to use the locale-support
  have to be found in your LIBS: (or KickROM).

  It's also a good idea to have a battery-backuped
  realtime-clock in your computer, otherwise it could
  be hard to keep track of time. But DRemind will also
  work without a battery clock if you have some Internet
  tool to set the time, or do it manually.


@endnode

@node Inst "Installation.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}How to install:@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

  Use the supplied installer-script!!

  ..or..

  @{u}DRemind:@{uu}

      DRemind should be placed in the WBStartup-drawer
      to accomplish most convenience.
      Otherwise there are no restrictions to its location
      in your system - just copy it wherever you like.

      A file called DRemind.image must be placed in the same
      directory where you have your prefs saved. Default
      prefs-directory is ENVARC: but can be changed from
      within DRemindPrefs.
      This image is read by datatypes and can therefor be in
      any format. Currently they are in IFF.
      - So what is this image for??
      - The original image is the ugly hand that appears everywhere
      in the GUI :) So now you can draw your own image and replace
      the DRemind.image with your picture! It should be 40*40 pixels
      otherwise it will be tiled or cut to fit in 40*40 pixels.

      There are currently 4 different images to choose from:
      - The original ugly "TheHand".
      - The "Boing" which is a boingball composed by Stefan Blixth.
      - And there are two versions of "NewHand", one 4-colour
        black & white and one 16(8)-colour with a red stripe
        around the finger.

NOTE: MUI and/or datatypes make a lock on the file and never lets
      it go, so if you want to replace it after you have started
      DRemind or DRPrefs you have to rename the old DRemind.image
      and then copy the new image there. After the next reboot you
      are able to remove the old, renamed image.

  @{u}DRemindPrefs:@{uu}

      DRemindPrefs should be placed in @{i}Sys:Prefs/ @{ui} if you
      want to be able to access it from DRemind.
      Also make a drawer for the goodies (if any) and enter that
      drawer in @{i}DRemindPrefs/Extras../Goodiepath.@{ui}
      Otherwise you could just copy it to the same
      directory as DRemindPrefs itself and you don't
      have to mess with the default Goodie-path.

  The catalog-files you prefer should be copied to your
  @{i}LOCALE:catalogs/@{fg shine}your country @{fg text}@{ui}directory.
  You'll have to do that by hand as I'm not familiar
  with the Installer. (I might be in the future though.. )


@endnode


@node RUse "Usage.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}How to use DRemind:@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

  When you start DRemind it will appear in Workbench's
  Tools-menu (if you didn't disable this function).
  If you select DRemind in the Tools-menu or press
  @{i}LeftAmiga Ctrl r @{ui}you will get a window
  with two listers and some buttons inside. See below:

  You can also control DRemind by sending it some @{"arexx" link Arexx}-commands.


 @{fg fill}@{u}DRemind main window@{uu}@{fg text}

  @{b}Standard Reminds@{ub}  - This is a list of all reminds created with DRemindPrefs.
                      You can doubleclick on a remind to open alittle info-
                      window and then click on the remind image to change state
                      of the remind you doubleclicked. If you doubleclicked
                      directly on the activation, time, date or remindstring
                      columns a editwindow will be opened for the thing you
                      doubleclicked on.

    @{b}Call prefs editor@{ub}     - Execute DRemindPrefs if it is located in
                            @{i}SYS:Prefs/DRemindPrefs@{ui}.

    @{b}Save@{ub}                  - Save the prefs. Useful it you de/activaded a
                            remind and don't want to start DRemindPrefs just
                            to save such a small change. You also have to save
                            if you deleted a remind and want to keep it deleted.

    @{b}Reload@{ub}                - Manually reloads the prefs-file.
                            This will also close the window if "Quit after saving prefs"
                            is selected in DRemindPrefs.

    @{b}Call Prefs and Reload@{ub} - Execute the prefeditor and then wait for it
                            to exit and than reload the prefs.
                            If "Quit after saving prefs" is selected in DRemindPrefs
                            then the window will be closed too.

  @{b}Temporary Reminds@{ub} - The list of temporary reminds.
                      This kind of reminds only have time and will be
                      deleted when popup'ed or if they get older than
                      24 hours and the @{i}Extras../Save temporary reminds@{ui}
                      is set in DRemindPrefs.

    @{i}<icon>@{ui}    - Opens a GUI for easy time editing.

    @{b}AM/PM@{ub}     - The AM or PM of the time if american time is selected
                in @{i}Extras../Timemode@{ui}.

    @{i}<string>@{ui}  - Here you can alter the time of the selected temporary
                remind. Remember to hit enter to get it into the list.

    @{i}<popdown>@{ui} - With this popdown menu you can pick a predefined amount
                of time to add to the time in the timefield for the
                selected temp-remind. Note that if you first pick +1
                minute and then +2 minutes, you will get +3 minutes
                in the end. With the topmost entry "Cancel" you can
                cancel the present action (but not the previous ones).

    @{i}<string>@{ui}  - Here you enter the info of what to be reminded about.
                Remember to hit enter to get it into the list.

    @{b}Add@{ub}       - Add a temporary remind.
                If you have created some predefined temporary reminds
                with DRemindPrefs, this button will become a popdown
                list containing all your predefined temp reminds.
                The top member in the list enables you to add a new
                blank temp remind.

    @{b}Delete@{ub}    - Delete a temporary remind.
    @{b}Clear All@{ub} - Delete all temporary reminds.
    @{b}Activate@{ub}  - This will activate the temporary remind you have just
                entered. Otherwise they will not be activated until you
                close the window by f.ex. pressing Continue.

  @{b}About@{ub}    - Some information about DRemind.
  @{b}Quit@{ub}     - Quit DRemind.
  @{b}Continue@{ub} - Hide DRemind in the background.


 @{fg fill}@{u}Reminder Window@{uu}@{fg text}

  The reminder window have some buttons in it when the MUI reminder
  window is used, and keys when the custom reminder window is used.
  These deserve some explanations too.

  @{b}Delete@{ub}        - This button is optional but when enabled it makes
                  it possible to delete the remind that just popped up.
                  This is the Del key for non-MUI reminders.

  @{b}Disable@{ub}       - This button is optional but when enabled it makes
                  it possible to disable the remind that just popped
                  up to prevent it from showing again if it is a
                  repetative reminds, such as a weekly remind.
                  This is the Tab key for non-MUI reminders.

  @{b}Remind again@{ub}  - This button is optional for normal reminds but
                  always exists for temporary reminds. Clicking it
                  will add a new temporary remind (regardless of
                  the original remind) so that you can get a new
                  remind within 24 hours.
                  Do not forget to set the time for the new temporary
                  remind!
                  This is the 'r' key for non-MUI reminders.

  @{b}No more today@{ub} - If some reminds are configured to pop up on startup
                  and the computer is rebooted repeatedly for some
                  reason it may be convenient to be able to force
                  these startup reminds to not appear any more this
                  day.
                  This is done by clicking the remind text in non-MUI reminders.

  @{b}OK@{ub}            - Confirms the remind and closes the remind window.
                  The Enter or Esc key works for this button.
                  This is the Esc key for non-MUI reminders.

  @{b}Prev@{ub}          - Shows the previous unconfirmed remind if more than
                  one remind has popped up without being closed.
                  It is possible to cycle through all popup'ed
                  reminds using this button without closing
                  anyone of them.
                  This is the 'p' key for non-MUI reminders.

  The Help key brings up some information for the non-MUI reminder
  window when it is open, containing the above information.


@endnode


@node Arexx "Arexx.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}The Arexx-commands:@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

  You can control some simple functions of DRemind with some arexx-commands.
  This is untested as I don't have the slightest idea of how to send an
  arexx-command to a program but here are the commands anyway:

  @{b}reload@{ub}    - This will reload the prefs-file from disk.
  @{b}save@{ub}      - This will save the prefs-file to your default location.
  @{b}callprefs@{ub} - This will start DRemindPrefs if it's in SYS:Prefs/
  @{b}disable@{ub}   - This will pause DRemind (as from the menuitem).
  @{b}enable@{ub}    - This will make a paused DRemind run again.
  @{b}clrtemp@{ub}   - This will remove all temporary reminds from the list.
  @{b}quit@{ub}      - This will quit DRemind.

  The port to where you should send these commands is "DREMIND".
  There is also another port called "DREMIND_RX.1" but this one
  is only used when DRemind is executing a arexx command as a
  remind.

  Note that these commands works the same way as if you where pressing
  one of the buttons in the GUI of DRemind..!


@endnode


@node PUse "Usage.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}How to use DRemindPrefs:@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

 @{fg fill}@{u}Main Page@{uu}@{fg text}

   @{i}<the lister>@{ui} - This is the list of all reminds.
                  You can configure what you like to see in this list
                  from the Main GUI settings. See the bottom of this page.
 
   @{b}Add@{ub}          - Add a remind to the bottom of the list.
 
   @{b}Delete@{ub}       - Remove a remind from the list.
 
   @{b}Clear All@{ub}    - Remove all reminds from the list.
                  (You will be warned before)
 
   @{b}Duplicate@{ub}    - Clone a remind and put the new one at the
                  bottom of the list.
 
   @{b}Search@{ub}       - Enter the search-gui:
     @{i}<the stringbevel>@{ui}   - The string to search for.
                           This will be compared to all text in the listview.
     @{b}Search from top@{ub}     - Will start the search from the top of the list.
     @{b}Search from current@{ub} - This will start the search from the active
                           remind and down. This works like a "search next"
                           function.
     @{b}Close@{ub}               - Close the search-gui.


   @{b}Load@{ub}         - Load last saved prefs.

   @{b}Save@{ub}         - Save prefs to the file specified in @{i}Extras../Prefspath:@{ui}.

   @{b}Export@{ub}       - This will open a window which you can use to export the remind
                  list into a text file. See @{fg fill}@{u}The menu@{uu}@{fg text} below for details.

   @{b}/\\ \\/@{ub}        - With these buttons you can push a remind up and down in
                  the lister. This is the closest you will get to drag'n'drop
                  which I wouldn't implement due to the way the remind-data
                  is stored in the program.
                  You can unhide this pair of buttons from the "Main GUI Settings".

   @{b}Date:@{ub}        - The date (or day) for the remind.

   @{b}Time:@{ub}        - The time for the remind.

   @{i}<icons>@{ui}      - Opens a GUI for easy date and time editing.

   @{b}AM/PM@{ub}        - The AM or PM of the time if american time is selected
                  in @{i}Extras../Timemode@{ui}.

   @{b}Use the specified date@{ub} / @{b}Use the startup date@{ub}
     Select whether to use the predefined date or the date when DRemind is started.

   @{b}Remind on Time@{ub} / @{b}Remind on Startup@{ub} / @{b}Remind once on Startup@{ub} /
   @{b}On Startup with Time@{ub} / @{b}Once on Startup with Time@{ub}
     Select whether to have the remind to pop up the specified time or
     when DRemind is started. Using "once", the remind will only popup
     when DRemind starts the first time the same day.
     You can also set it to both pop up when you start your computer
     and at a specific time.
 
   Setting "Use the startup date" and "Remind on Startup/once" will make
   DRemind popup the remind immediately at the next startup of DRemind.

   @{b}What to remind about:@{ub}
     This is the remind string that will show when the remind
     pops up.

   @{b}B@{ub} @{i}I @{ui}@{u}U@{uu} @{fg shine}C @{fg fill}C @{fg back}C@{fg text}
     Use these buttons to apply different styles and colours
     to your reminds to be able to spot them easier in the list.

   @{b}Remind active:@{ub} - Set if this remind should be active or not.
                    You can click in the leftmost, activation, column
                    to toggle this.

   @{b}RemindType:@{ub}    - Select the type of remind:
     @{u}Single@{uu}          - This type will only come up once and be inactivated or
                       if @{i}Extras../Delete passed Single-reminds@{ui} is
                       selected it will be deleted.
     @{u}Daily@{uu}           - This type will pop up every day of the week if no days
                       are disabled in @{i}Remind-options@{ui}.
     @{u}Weekly@{uu}          - This type will pop up a specific day every week.
     @{u}Monthly@{uu}         - This type will pop up a specific day every month
                       unless no month is disabled in @{i}Remind-options@{ui}.
     @{u}Yearly@{uu}          - This type will pop up a specific date every year.
     @{u}Day interval@{uu}    - This is a special remind which will pop up with
                       a certain number of days interval specified in
                       @{i}Remind-options@{ui}.
     @{u}Time interval@{uu}   - This is a special remind which will pop up frequently
                       with a specified time interval specified in
                       @{i}Remind-options@{ui}.
 
 
   @{i}@{b}GenID @{ub}@{ui}- This is actually a debug-button but I left this in the public
           distribution because a bug in earlier versions of DRemindPrefs
           made it possible for multiple reminds to have the same ID-number
           which caused malfunction in "Remind ONCE at startup" so if you
           have problem with Once-reminds then press this button and you
           will be told how many incorrect ID-numbers you had and at the
           same time all ID-numbers will be regenerated.

   @{b}Show Date@{ub}         - This will show the present date and
                       time in a requester.
 
   @{b}Get Date@{ub}          - This will set the @{i}Date:@{ui} and @{i}Time:@{ui} fields
                       to the present date and time.

   @{b}Main GUI settings@{ub} - See the bottom of this page.

   @{b}Quit@{ub}              - Quit DRemindPrefs. A requester will pop up
                       if you activated @{i}Extras../Enable Quit-requester@{ui}.


 @{fg fill}@{u}Options@{uu}@{fg text} - Only affects individual reminds.

   @{fg shine}Permanent options:@{fg text}

     @{b}Activation@{ub}     - This is only active if the remind is set on startup.
       Remind Any time!             - The startup-remind will pop up
                                      whenever you start DRemind no matter
                                      what time it is.
       Only remind Before this time - The remind will only pop up if
                                      DRemind is started before the
                                      time specified below.
       Only remind After this time  - The remind will only pop up if
                                      DRemind is started after the time
                                      specified below.
 
     @{b}Radio buttons@{ub}  - With this you can choose if you want to
                      execute a file along with the remind-window
                      or just execute a file.
       Pop up window                - Just open the remind-window.
       Execute file                 - Just execute a file.
       Both window & file           - Open the remind-window AND execute
                                      a file.

     @{b}File:@{ub}          - The program to execute which should be a
                      CLI-program with eventual arguments.

     @{b}Pri:@{ub}           - Priority of the program.

     @{b}ARexx@{ub}
       @{b}Use arexx@{ub}    - If you want to send an ARexx command at remind.
 
       @{b}Only arexx@{ub}   - Activating this only an ARexx command will be sent.
                      No remind-window will be opened and no file will
                      be executed.
 
       @{b}Command:@{ub}     - The ARexx command to be sent.
 
       @{b}Port:@{ub}        - The port the command should be sent to.


   @{fg shine}Type-specific options:@{fg text}

     @{u}Single:@{uu}
       @{i}slider @{ui}            - The number of days before the actual remind
                            you want DRemind to start popping up pre-reminds.
       @{b}Inactivate@{ub}         - This will simply set the slider to 0 days.
       @{i}cycle @{ui}             - Here you can set when you want all these
                            pre-reminds to pop up in the day.
         Remind on Time         - Reminds you on time.
         Remind on Startup      - Reminds you on every startup the
                                  same day.
         Remind once on startup - Reminds you only on the first startup
                                  the same day.

     @{u}Daily:@{uu}
       @{b}Weekdays@{ub}           - Which days of the week you want the
                            daily-remind to pop up.
       @{b}Include all days@{ub}   - Make the remind to pop up every day.

     @{u}Weekly:@{uu}
       none

     @{u}Monthly:@{uu}
       @{b}Months@{ub}             - Which months of the year you want the
                            remind to pop up.
       @{b}Include all months@{ub} - Make the remind to pop up every month.

     @{u}Yearly:@{uu}
       @{b}Additional remind@{ub}  - Set this to a positive number of days
                            to get an extra yearly remind the specified
                            number of days after the real one.
                            Set it to a negative number and you will
                            get an extra remind the number of days
                            before the real one.
                            Set it to 0 to inactivate this feature.
       @{b}Inactivate@{ub}         - This button, and the cycle gadget below works
                            like described for @{u}Single:@{uu}-reminds.

     @{u}Day interval:@{uu}
       @{b}Day frequency@{ub}      - The interval in days between the reminds.

     @{u}Time interval:@{uu}
       @{b}Time interval@{ub}      - The interval in hours and minutes
                            between the reminds.


 @{fg fill}@{u}Extras..@{uu}@{fg text} - Global program-settings..

   @{fg shine}Settings@{fg text}

     @{b}Date format@{ub} - How you like the date to be displayed.
  
     @{b}Time mode@{ub}   - If you want american or real time.
  
     @{b}Delete passed Single-reminds@{ub}
        If you want old Single-reminds to be deleted.
  
     @{b}Delete temp-reminds upon exit@{ub}
        If you want to delete eventually saved temporary remind when
        you quit DRemind.
  
     @{b}DisplayBeep when reminding@{ub}
        If you want a boing and your screen flashed when a remind pops up.
  
     @{b}Report all errors@{ub}
        This will report all minor errors as well, like if temp-remind
        file didn't save and so on.


   @{fg shine}Preferences@{fg text}

     @{b}Use Workbench Appmenu in the Tools-menu@{ub}
        If you want DRemind iconified in the Tools-menu in workbench.

     @{b}Pop WB to front when a remind pops up@{ub}
        If you want Workbench-screen to front when a remind pops up.

     @{b}Make DRemind add a temp remind when un-iconified@{ub}
        If you select this then everytime you uniconify DRemind by
        selecting it from the Tools-menu or use the hotkey DRemind
        will automatically switch to the Temporary Reminds page and
        initiate a temporary remind for you. Often the only reason
        for opening DRemind's window is because you want to add a
        temp remind and then this simplify this alot.

     @{b}Remember temporary reminds after reboot@{ub}
        If you want the temporary remind that can only be created from
        DRemind itself to be saved. This is useful if you specify such
        a remind and you restart your computer, they will be forgotten
        otherwize in case of a reboot.
        In any case, a temp-remind is of Single-type so they will be
        deleted when popped up even if saved or if they get more than
        24 hours old..   They are not save in DRemind.prefs.

     @{b}Quit after saving prefs (DRemind closes after reload)@{ub}
        If you select this then DRemindPrefs will immediately quit when
        you have saved your reminds, i.e. pressed "Save". DRemind will
        automatically close it's window after you have reloaded prefs
        from within DRemind when this checkmark is selected.

     @{b}Enable warning requester when quitting@{ub}
        If you want to be prompted when you try to quit.
        This will also enable a requester asking you to quit
        after saving prefs.

     @{b}Remind check interval in seconds@{ub}
        Number of seconds between DRemind loops through the remindlist.
        Lower value, higher accurancy, slightly more CPU-load.


   @{fg shine}Look@{fg text}

     @{b}Reminder@{ub}            - How much info (and garbage) you want the
                           remind-windows to show.
                           "Extended" is quite verbal.
                           "Normal" just shows all important info.
                           "Restricted" only shows the remind string.

     @{b}Use MUI reminder window@{ub}
        If you want the remind-window to look more like a requester
        instead of a window. It can be closed by pressing Enter or
        Esc. The original window (i.e. when unselecting this option)
        is closed by Esc only.

     @{b}Use you selected font for the remind text@{ub}
        If this is selected your selected font (at the bottom of the
        preferences window Extras..-page) will be used for the remind
        text in the MUI reminder window. If not, the default font (which
        is used everywhere else) will be used.
  
     @{b}Use you selected font for other fields@{ub}
        If you want to use your selected font for the other fields, like
        the date, time, remind type information in the MUI reminder window.
  
     @{b}Use you selected font for the buttons@{ub}
        If you want to use your selected font for the buttons in the MUI
        reminder window.

     @{b}Temporary Start->Once button@{ub}
        If you enable this you will be able to force a Startup-remind
        to not pop up anymore until the next day.  This is very
        useful if you sometimes reboot very often and don't want a
        particular remind to pop up anymore until the next day again.
        To do this temporary disabling, just click on the remind-text
        in the original remind-window or on the button "No more today"
        in the "system-like" (MUI) requester when the remind pops up.
  
     @{b}Delete- & Disable-buttons@{ub}
        With this checkmark selected you will get a Delete- and a
        Disable-button in all reminders. If you're using the
        standard-reminder (non-MUI) the Del- and Tab-keys on your
        keyboard is used instead. Del for delete and Tab for disable.
  
        This could be useful if you f.ex wanna set up a Daily remind
        to remind you every day about something that has to be done,
        and when you eventually have got yourself to to this thing
        you can just delete the remind, or disable it for future use,
        without having to start DRemindPrefs!

     @{b}Remind again-button for normal reminds@{ub}
        When this is enabled a button making it possible to add a
        new temporary remind from the currently popped up remind
        will be shown.

        This is useful if you like to be reminded about the same
        thing again a little later the same day without adjusting
        the original remind.


   @{b}Goodiepath:@{ub}         - Where to find the DRemind goodies.
                         (Currently there are no goodies :-(  I will
                         see what I can do about that in the future.)

   @{b}Use DRemind goodies@{ub} - If you want to use the goodies.
                         (see above)

   @{b}PrefsPath:@{ub}          - Where to save the reminds.
      This directory is also used to put all temp-files that
      DRemind generates to keep track of "startup once" reminds
      and temporary reminds. It is also in this directory you
      should put the file DRemind.image which is an image of
      40*40 pixels in any format. See @{"Installation" link Inst} for details.

   @{b}Get old path@{ub}        - Automatically move DRemind.prefs from a previously
                         defined path and save it in the old place.

   @{b}Remind font@{ub}         - Use a font-requester to pick a new font to use
                         with DRemind. (The normal GUI's wouldn't be
                         affected, use MUI settings instead.)


 @{fg fill}@{u}Temp reminds@{uu}@{fg text} - Create predefine temporary reminds

    @{u}Preconfigured temporary reminds @{uu}

     @{i}<the lister>@{ui} - This is the list of all temporary reminds.
                    This list has two columns, one with the remind
                    text for you predefined temporary reminds, and
                    one with the amount of time that the temp
                    remind should wait. The remind string and the
                    time can be adjusted when actually picking a
                    temp remind for use, this time is only default
                    values.

     @{b}Add@{ub}          - Add a new temp remind. Use the string gadgets above
                    to enter the remind text and time. The time field
                    also has the same popdown list as the time
                    setting for the temp reminds within DRemind.

     @{b}Detele@{ub}       - Remove a temp remind.

     @{b}Clear All@{ub}    - Remove all temp reminds. NOTE: There is no warning
                    and no undo! If you cleared the list by accident
                    you can get back what you last saved by clicking
                    Load on the Main page, or from the menu.



 @{fg fill}@{u}Main GUI settings@{uu}@{fg text} - Customizing the main window

  @{fg shine}Lister, Sort@{fg text}

    @{u}Remind-lister settings@{uu}

      @{b}State@{ub}  - If the on/off state is to be shown in the list.
      @{b}Type@{ub}   - If the remind-type is to be shown in the list.
      @{b}Date@{ub}   - If the date is to be shown in the list.
      @{b}Time@{ub}   - If the time is to be shown in the list.
      @{b}Remind@{ub} - If the remind-string is to be shown in the list.

    @{u}Sort@{uu}

      Just press the button you want to sort by.

      @{b}Auto sort list by@{ub} - Here you can set if and what you want the list
                          to be autosorted by. Auto sort will be performed
                          whenever you change any remind data that is set
                          to be auto sorted by, or when you add a remind.

      @{b}2nd sort@{ub}          - Here you can set what the sort routine should
                          sort by if it finds two alike entries when sorting.

      @{b}Reverse sorting@{ub}   - If you want the sort to be up-side-down.

      @{b}Unsort@{ub}            - This will undo the sorting. Undo-information
                          is also saved in the prefsfile so that you can
                          unsort tomorrow what you sorted today.
                          Use Lock sort to set a new unsort point.

      @{b}Lock sort@{ub}         - Set the current list order as the unsort point.
                          This mean that any sorting you did after clicking
                          this button will be unsortable back to the point
                          when you clicked this button.


  @{fg shine}Show'n'Hide@{fg text}

    In this part of the program you can personalize DRemindPrefs by deciding
    what should be shown in the GUI and not. Very good if you have some
    buttons that you hardly ever use, then you can hide them :-)
    Some buttons are hidden by default!

    Just double click on the item in the list and the GUI will immediately
    change and adapt.
    
    Don't remove too much from the window, MUI has a tendency to be a bit
    unstable in such cases :(


 @{fg fill}@{u}The menu@{uu}@{fg text}

  @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}

    @{b}Load@{ub}              - Same as the "Load" button in the window.
    @{b}Save@{ub}              - Same as the "Save" button in the window.
    @{b}Main GUI Settings@{ub} - Same as the "Main GUI settings" button in
                        the window.
    @{b}MUI-Settings...@{ub}   - Opens the MUI prefs editor. There you can
                        change the look of buttons, sliders and
                        windows etc., as you might know from other
                        MUI applications.

    @{b}About@{ub}             - Some informations about the program.
    @{b}About MUI@{ub}         - Same as above but concerning MUI.
    @{b}OnyxSoft@{ub}          - Just more informations :)
    @{b}Quit@{ub}              - Same as the "Quit" button in the window.

  @{fg shine}Tools@{fg text}

    The following five items function as the corresponding buttons
    in the window:

     @{b}Add
     Delete
     Clear All
     Dublicate
     Search@{ub}

    @{b}Export remind list@{ub}

      This will open a window which you can use to export the remind
      list into a text file.

      @{i}string@{ui}
        Here you can enter a string of how you want the lines in your
        exported file to be.
        You have 7 switches to use when constucting your string:

        %a - This will insert the state of a remind. This will be
             "On" or "Off" (with the english catalog).
        %r - This will insert the remind type of a remind. This will
             be "Single", "Daily" or "Weekly" etc...
        %d - This will insert the date the same way as you have
             specified it for the remind list.
        %t - This will insert the time in the same way as in the list.
        %s - This will insert the actual remind string that you have
             type for a remind.
        %o - This will insert a string with the remind options. The
             string will look the same way as it does at the bottom
             of the main window when you have "Options short information"
             set to Show in "Main GUI Settings".
        %% - This will insert a percent sign (%).

      @{b}Save in columns@{ub}
        This will fill out each line with spaces after every switch
        so that the file will be easy to read. Test and see!

      @{b}Export as...@{ub}
        This will open an ASL-requester asking you for a file to
        export your remind list to.

      @{b}Close@{ub}
        This will close the window.


@endnode

@node RNote "Notes.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}Changes, notes and features in DRemind:@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

  @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Fixed a very long-standing bug that caused instability if
          the settings flag "Delete passed single reminds" were activated.
          Thanks to Stellan Pistoor and Samir Hawamdeh for reporting
          and testing.

  @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Updated Italian catalogs and installer script thanks to
          Samir Hawamdeh.

  @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} Changed the hotkey so that it can be used with only one
          hand. It is now LeftAmiga+Ctrl+r.

  @{b}v1.71@{ub}

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Quitting DRemind from Commodities Exchange made DRemind crash.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Added more error-checking when loading and saving prefs as I
     have now seen two reports about misbehaviour that I can only
     relate to read or write error of the prefs file.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} The image wasn't loaded correctly.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Raised the stack some more as the JIT on OS4 combined with
     heavy MUI settings could be too much sometimes.

  @{b}v1.70@{ub}

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} It is now possible to create and save pre-defined temporary
     reminds to pick and use whenever it suits.
     Let's say you often want to quickly cool a drink in the
     freezer. This takes about 10 minutes. Then you can
     create a temporary remind with a +0:10h time called
     "Drink in freezer!" and use this from a handy pop-down
     meny whenever you like!

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Now it is possible to create a new temporary remind out
     of every normal popped up remind by clicking "Remind again".
     Useful if you are unable to handle the issue right now
     but like to be reminded later the same day.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Added a feature to peak into other popped up reminds behind
     the currently visible popped up remind without closing it.
     It is hence possible to cycles through multiple popped
     reminds without closing any of them.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Updated Spanish and French translations thanks to
     Javier de las Rivas <javierdlr@euskalnet.net> and Hervé Cordialement
     <herve.dpt@free.fr>.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Fixed a crash if DRemind was started with an empty or damaged
     prefs file, or with Goodies ticked but unavailable.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Fixed Time interval reminds when set to "Remind at startup".
     They opened continuously instead of following its time
     interval after the startup remind had shown.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Yearly pre- and post reminds (i.e. birthdays) was never
     announced as pre- or post reminds.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Fixed some other bugs regarding yearly reminds.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} The remind image was not shown on systems with faked
     chipmem in the custom remind window.

  @{b}v1.68@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Updated MicroReminder that is in this same archive.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a feature that makes it possible to set a temp remind
    to remind again after it has popped up. A button in the
    MUI reminder window makes this possible.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Increased the stack of DRemind a bit to prevent it from crashing
    when editing MUI settings or executing DRemindPrefs from within
    DRemind under OS4.

  @{b}v1.67@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can make your remind *Bold*, /Italic/, _Underlined_
    and/or coloured in the remind list!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a bug which caused Single reminds to never pop up.
    (a 2<->4 digits year bug)

  @{b}v1.66@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can use your selected remind font for the MUI
    reminder window too! See "DRPrefs/Extras/Remind Window"
    for settings. (I have got a request for expanding the
    preference of the look of the remind window further but
    that will be in another version.)

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Changing values for a remind directly in DRemind did show
    in the list window even though the change took place.

  @{b}v1.65@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added info so it is possible to see if a single remind has
    a preremind specified.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} A single remind was deleted or disabled when the first
    preremind popped up preventing followind prereminds and the
    real remind to pop up.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now the real date is shown for single and yearly reminds
    when using prereminds instead of the calculated date
    from the number of pre/post days.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Changed the timer unit to use VBlank instead of MicroHz.

  @{b}v1.64@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} If you use the "Make DRemind add a temp remind when un-
    iconified"-feature DRemind will now automatically switch
    to the normal remind list if the first thing you do is
    delete this automatic temp-remind.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can press enter to close a remind that has popped
    up instead of "o" for "Ok". Esc still works too ofcourse.

  @{b}v1.63@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now, when adding a temporary remind, you can also press Tab
    in the Time-field to get on as long as you press enter in
    the Remind-string-field. Before you had to press enter in
    both the time- and remind-strings (which BTW is still simpler).

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can get directly to the Temporary reminds page and
    have a temporary remind automatically initiated when you
    uniconify DRemind! See DRemindPrefs.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} A few days ago I implemented the same arexx-command support
    DRemind uses in another program only to discover that it
    doesn't work at all! What I'm talking about is not the
    "execute arexx as a remind" thing, but the commands you can
    send to DRemind to invoke it to do certain things.
    Now it finally works. It was very easy to fix (I just
    needed to know how).

  @{b}v1.62@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The time in the GUI wasn't updated for temp-remind when
    DRemind was started and loaded temp-reminds from the tempfile.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Time-interval reminds didn't work quite as they should
    have. Now they should.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now DRemind is no longer using the battclock.resource
    which means that people without a battery clock, who f.ex get the
    time from the Internet, can use the DRemind too.

  @{b}v1.61@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} New icons! I called the drawer OS3.9. They are now also
    the default.

  @{b}v1.6@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The button "No More Today" for reminds at startup didn't
    work. Fixed.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Moved a requester string to the catalog that I had forgot
    about. It's called R_REMHELP in the catalog.

  @{b}v1.59@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Major bug made no reminds set to pop up on startup to pop up at
    all! Fixed!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Reminds set to both time and startup could have poped up at
    random. Fixed.

  @{b}v1.58@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Delete and disable a remind that has just popped up didn't
    work, now it should.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can press the help key in a remind window to get some
    help about what keys you can use to control a remind window.

  @{b}v1.57@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} There has always been something that has been causing an
    enforcer hit in DRemind. That should now be gone forever!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} I reversed the remindqueue so that the latest remind that
    popped up always shows and earlier unclosed remind windows
    will show again when you close the currently opened remind
    window.

  @{b}v1.56@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Must have messed up some logical expression somewhere
    because many reminds with certain settings never popped up
    before. This should now be fixed.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Alexander Döller has been very kind and made the installer
    we have all been waiting for! Thank you very much :-)

  @{b}v1.55@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can edit the date, time and remind-string directly
    from DRemind without starting DRemindPrefs! Just doubleclick
    on a column in the lister.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Aldo Bianchi has been very kind and made some nice MagicWB
    and OS3.5 GlowIcons for DRemind and it's prefseditor!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} There has been a bugfix for Greve Axel's MRemind-GUI
    for MicroReminder!

  @{b}v1.54b@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now there are 2 more nice DRemind.image's; "NewHand B&W", a
    4 colour black and white hand and "NewHand Red", the same
    hand but with a red knot around the finger instead of black
    and white. These hands look nothing like the old ugly hand.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a Cancel option in the popup lister for picking a time
    when making a temporary remind. Good if you keep the DRemind
    window at the bottom of the screen and therefor cannot reach
    the popup button to close the lister..

  @{b}v1.54a@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a serious bug a user reported which caused the GUI
    to stop respond if the file DRemind.temps (for temp-
    reminds) existed!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now DRemind doesn't autosave when you delete a remind
    directly from DRemind's info-window.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} MicroReminder is back, and now with a nice little arexx
    GUI made by Axel Greve!

  @{b}v1.54@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Localization has been changed in some parts so that
    it will look good in all languages.
    ! Translators, please read the Translators.readme !

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can finally edit the ugly hand!
    The file DRemind.image now contains this image!
    See @{"Installation" link Inst} for details.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now it is optional if you want to delete
    eventually saved temporary reminds when you quit
    DRemind.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Executing an arexx command as a remind now works!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can have a remind to pop up both on
    startup @{u}and@{uu} at a specific time!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The pre/post-reminds in Yearly remind mode now
    reminds every day from the day set and to the actual
    remind!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Single remind also has pre-remind!

  @{b}v1.53@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} When "Enable Quit-requester" is selected in the prefs,
    also DRemind will be affected when quitting.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Apparently I missunderstood the concept of time with
    AM/PM but have now been corrected and so should also
    DRemind have been.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a button to activate recently added temporary
    reminds without having to close the window.

  @{b}v1.52@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a possibility to get a Delete and Disable button
    directly in every reminder-window!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added some arexx-commands for external control!

  @{b}v1.50@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now using the fabolus MUI as GUI-engine!
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added ability to execute an Arexx-command as remind!
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Improved remindviewer in DRemind with doubleclick!
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can use the menu item "Disable" to pause DRemind!
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can select delay for temporary reminds much easier!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} DRemind now has Goodie-support which means that you can
    put the DRemind goodies in the selected goodie-drawer and
    DRemind will load them on startup.
    A goodie is a little program containing a remind specific
    for a certain happening of the year, like christmas :-)
    This has to be activated from DRemindPrefs.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can temporary transform a "Remind on startup"-remind
    to a "Remind ONCE"-remind!  This is done by in the original
    remind-window close the window by clicking on the actual
    remind-text.  In the "system-like" requester an adition
    button is made. This has to be activated from DRemindPrefs.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You are able to switch between real time (also
    called "military" time) and american time with AM/PM!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} If you have a remind to start at startup you can set if
    it should only popup before or after a certain time!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You don't have to type in date and time by hand,
    just click on the icon next to the field you want to alter and
    a window with sliders will appear!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The yearly-remind has now an option to set an extra
    remind a number of days before or after the actual
    remind.  So one wouldn't forget to f.ex. buy presents
    in time for a birthday or so!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can now select between three different ways of
    putting up the remind:
    Extended - The original remind with "See you tomorrow.."
               and all the other kind of meaningless lines.
    Normal - This only tells you what type of remind,
             date, time and ofcourse the remind.
    Restricted - This only shows the remind, no type or date.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} DRemind is now completely font- and hack-sensitive
    regarding window-sizes and so!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The date now also has a startup-option just as the time!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can decide what will be shown in the lister.
    Not only "(On ) remind.." can be used but all basics of
    a remind like date and time!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can start a program with argument when a
    remind should or are popping up! You can select
    "Pop up window", "Start program" or both if you want!!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can set reminds that pops up on startup to
    just once that day you have specified the remind
    to popup!  Useful if you often restart your computer.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The prefs-editor should be called "DRemindPrefs" and lie in
    "SYS:Prefs/" or you won't be able to start it from DRemind!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can get info about reminds by double-clicking on them.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Saved temporary reminds will be deleted when you quit DRemind
    or if you start DRemind and the saved temp-reminds are older
    than one day.


@endnode

@node PNote "Notes.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}Changes and notes in DRemindPrefs:@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

  @{fg fill}* FIX *@{fg text} The temporary reminds was not loaded if there were no regular
          reminds saved.

  @{b}v2.71@{ub}

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Quitting DRemindPrefs from Commodities Exchange didn't work.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Added more error-checking when loading and saving prefs as I
     have now seen two reports about misbehaviour that I can only
     relate to read or write error of the prefs file.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Without a prefs file the default look of the GUI was not
     initialized.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} Raised the stack some more as the JIT on OS4 combined with
     heavy MUI settings could be too much sometimes.

  @{b}v2.70@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a new page on which you can create predefined
    temporary reminds.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a bad crash that occured if a blank or damaged
    prefs file was present when DRemindPrefs was started.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Restructured  some small parts of the GUI to make it
    look better and be easier to understand.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Change default font from Topaz to Helvetica.

  @{b}v2.68@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a hit that occoured if you started and quit
    DRemindPrefs without having any reminds or prefs file.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Increased the stack a bit to make it more rubust under OS4.

  @{b}v2.67@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can make your remind *Bold*, /Italic/ and/or
    _Underlined_ in the remind list!
    See Main GUI Settings/Show'n'Hide to make the gadgets
    visible. (The extra space to the right of these buttons
    is a workaround for a show/hide group layout bug in MUI.)

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} --BAR--'s couldn't be moved since they where excluded from
    the sorting routines. Fixed.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Which gadgets to be shown as default was not correct.
    See Main GUI Settings/Show'n'Hide for other gadgets.

  @{b}v2.66@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added further settings for the MUI remind window as it now
    can use your selected font too!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now it is possible to sort the list without messing up the
    bar labels you might have put in the list to separate your
    different kinds of reminds!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a Button to lock the sorting, meaning that if you have
    a prefered order you can lock this order so that Unsort will
    revert to this locked order instead of some previous old order.

  @{fg fill}**@{fg text} .cd file slightly updated because of the changes.

  @{b}v2.65@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The "Remind on .." cyclegadget was not updated for the single-
    and yearly- reminds' extra reminds on the options page.

  @{b}v2.64@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can add bars in the list to make it easier to separate
    different types of reminds like birthdays, TV-programs,
    appointments etc.
    Translators: Addition to the catalog has been made because
                 of this feature. Sorry for the high update
                 frequency.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed the GenID button the was not hidden at startup even
    if you have selected so.

  @{b}v2.63@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added the "Export" button in the main window for exporting
    the remind list. This exactly works like the "Export remind
    list" item from the "Tools" menu.
 
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Several locale calls used the "\\\\d" switch for inserting
    numbers, where needed. As this is converted just to "\\d" in the
    output strings the switch has been corrected to "%ld".
 
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed the bug with the lost remind. I rewrote the list-
    display in the last release so that the list actually doesn't
    store anything anymore. But something has to be stored so I
    used the actual position, but the first position is 0 which
    MUI takes as an error and ignores, this is why one item was
    always lost ;)

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added a switch to make DRemind open on the Temporary Reminds
    page and initiate a new temporary remind everytime it is
    uniconified. Can be useful if that's usually the only reason
    you uniconify DRemind.

    Translators: Additions and corrections to DRemindPrefs.cd
                 have been made because of some of theese features.

  @{b}v2.62@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can export the remind list into a text file!
    You decide yourself exactly how you want your file to look like.
    Translators: Addition to the catalog has been made because of this
                 feature.

  @{b}v2.61@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Version string said v2.5 in v2.6, fixed. Otherwise just
    updated version number to keep up with DRemind...

  @{b}v2.6@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Made a slight change to the string OG_DELBUT in the catalog.

  @{b}v2.59@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Nothing is new in DRemindPrefs, only bumped version to be
    in sync with DRemind...

  @{b}v2.58@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can make the list to auto-sort whenever you
    change anything in it.

  @{b}v2.57@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can select what you want the lister to be
    secondly sorted by when you sort the list.

  @{b}v2.56@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you don't have to press enter in the stringgadgets
    for filename and arexx command and port. You still need
    to when editing the remindstring, time and date though.

  @{b}v2.55@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you will see the weekday for all reminds that uses
    date with day, month and possibly year!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a few bugs..

  @{b}v2.54a@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Removed a tag in the GUI that made the optional info-
    string on the main page get the wrong background.

  @{b}v2.54@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now also the bubble-help has been localized!
    ! Translators, please read the Translators.readme !

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now it is optional if you want to delete
    (eventually) saved temporary reminds when you quit
    DRemind.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can finally edit the ugly hand!
    The file DRemind.image now contains this image!
    See @{"Installation" link Inst} for details.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can have a remind to pop up both on
    startup @{u}and@{uu} at a specific time!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The pre/post-reminds in Yearly remind mode now
    reminds every day from the day set and to the actual
    remind!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Single remind also has pre-remind!

  @{b}v2.53@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} All listviews can now get properly resized!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added arrow-buttons that you can use to push a remind
     up and down in the list!  The buttons is default hidden
     but can be shown through @{ "Main GUI Settings" link PUse}.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Added an auto-quit option so that DRemindPrefs will
     quit immediately when you press save!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Apparently I missunderstood the concept of time with
     AM/PM but have now been corrected and so should also
     DRemind have been.

  @{b}v2.52@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now you can, using the "Main GUI setting", add a
     string at the bottom of the GUI that immediatly
     tells you what extra options your selected remind
     has, i.e you don't need to flip to the Options
     page to se this anymore!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Fixed a bug in the time-string of the "remind only
     before/after" section in the Options page..

  @{b}v2.51@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Addad a possibility to get a Delete and Disable button
     directly in every reminder-window! See the Extras page.

  @{b}v2.5@{ub}

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Now using the fabolus MUI as GUI-engine!
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can select which gadgets you want in the main window!
  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} Will adjust the GUI for your screen if it is to small!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} It's possible to choose between 4 different
    date-modes: dd-mmm-(yy)yy  [the old one],
    dd-mm-(yy)yy, mm-dd-(yy)yy and (yy)yy-mm-dd!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You are able to switch between real time (or so
    called "military" time) and 12-hour clock with AM/PM!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} If you have a remind to start at startup you can set if
    it only should popup before or after a certain time!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You don't have to type in date and time by hand,
    just click on the icon next to the field you want to alter
    and a window with slider will appear!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The yearly-remind has an option to set an extra
    remind a number of days before or after the actual
    remind.  So one wouldn't forget to f.ex. buy presents
    in time for a birthday or so!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can select between three different ways of
    putting up the remind:
    Extended - The original remind with "See you tomorrow.."
               and all the other kind of pointless lines.
    Normal - This only tells you what type of remind,
             date, time and ofcourse the remind.
    Restricted - This only shows the remind, no type or date.

    All three option works both with "my" window and the
     "system"-requester.

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The Date- and Time-fields are very flexible in
    interpretation of the input!
    F.ex. you can type '1/6-98' and it will be converted to
    01-06-1998 and so on..

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can press "Dublicate" instead of "Add" to create
    a new remind with the selected reminds all settings!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The date now also has a startup-option just as the time!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can decide what will be shown in the lister.
    Not only "(On ) remind.." can be used but all basics of
    a remind like date and time!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can sort the reminds by remind, state, date, time,
    or type depending on what you have visible in the lister!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can search for the occurence of a string the is
    somwhere in the lister!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} The "Remind-option"-button is available for all
    reminds and in it you can select the usual plus a file
    to be started with every remind!  You select if you
    only want the remind to pop up as before or if you
    want to start a program instead, or do both!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can set the time-field to not only 12:34 and
    'Start' but also 'Once' which means that the remind
    will only popup on startup the @{i}first @{ui}time you start
    your computer every day and not every reboot as with 'Start'!

  @{fg fill}*@{fg text} You can Activate/Inactivate a remind by doubleclicking on it.


@endnode

@node RBugs "Bugs.."

    @{fg shine}@{b}Bugs in DRemind:@{ub}
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

  The old image is always used in the non-MUI reminder.

  MUI and/or datatypes makes a lock on the DRemind.image file but
  never unlock it and I don't know what to do about it, I never
  touch the file myself within the program.

  If you find any, just mail me and tell me what the problem is!
  And please give as much information as possible. Thankyou.


@endnode

